    <stitle>ALTERNATOR: DELCO-REMY 25-SI SERIES, TYPES 400 AND 450 - REPAIR PROCEDURES - DIODE CHECKS</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="check" graphiccount="0">
        <title>DIODE CHECKS</title>
        <para>Check each of the six diodes by removing each diode lead from the stud and connecting an ohmmeter using
            the lower range scale (Rx1 or Rx10) to the diode lead and case (Item C,
            <hotlnk document="s08014_6.xml" xrefid="f0801407">Figure 7</hotlnk>). Then reverse the ohmmeter lead
            connections to the diode lead and case. If both readings are the same, replace the diode. A good diode will
            give one high and one low reading.
        </para>
    </svcproc>
